    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chorizo is golden and crispy, add the<strong> diced shallot</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>orzo</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up until the grains are fully coated</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 16-17 min, stirring continuously, or until the stock is fully absorbed and the orzo is cooked with a slight bite</p>",
